Newcastle United will be in a position to extend Matty Longstaff and Andy Carroll's current deals until the end of play this season with the campaign set to run beyond their existing contracts.<br />
<br />
Following the Premier League meeting at the start of this week, a statement read: &ldquo;At Monday's Shareholders' meeting, Premier League clubs unanimously agreed to be allowed to renegotiate and enter into short term contract extensions with players whose deals are due to expire on 30 June of this year.&quot;

